143
00:08:16.551 --> 00:08:21.891
Since each side is 30 minutes, Nishimoto-san
probably died within the last 30 minutes.

144
00:08:22.701 --> 00:08:23.831
Conan-kun.

145
00:08:24.441 --> 00:08:26.301
Look next to Nishimoto-san's feet.

146
00:08:26.301 --> 00:08:26.801
Huh?

147
00:08:28.121 --> 00:08:29.261
Sheet music.

148
00:08:31.131 --> 00:08:33.261
What does it say this time?

149
00:08:34.081 --> 00:08:35.061
"Suicide note."

150
00:08:36.031 --> 00:08:40.221
Suicide note? You mean Nishimoto-san...

151
00:08:40.851 --> 00:08:42.651
He killed himself, huh?

152
00:08:43.011 --> 00:08:48.621
According to this note, he regretted
killing Kawashima and Kuroiwa.

153
00:08:48.621 --> 00:08:51.231
So it was Nishimoto who killed them.

154
00:08:52.031 --> 00:08:56.661
His motive was that he
didn't want the mistake

155
00:08:56.661 --> 00:08:59.201
he committed with Kawashima,
Kuroiwa, Kameyama,

156
00:08:59.201 --> 00:09:04.221
who died two years ago, and Aso,

157
00:09:04.221 --> 00:09:06.461
who killed himself 12 years ago, to be exposed.

158
00:09:06.721 --> 00:09:09.131
Even the pianist Aso?

159
00:09:09.131 --> 00:09:10.261
Yeah.

160
00:09:10.261 --> 00:09:14.221
It says that Aso came up with the code.

161
00:09:14.221 --> 00:09:18.571
They must've done something using this code.

162
00:09:18.571 --> 00:09:19.941
I see.

163
00:09:19.941 --> 00:09:25.481
Nishimoto believed the sheet music that
survived the fire described their old secret.

164
00:09:25.481 --> 00:09:29.611
In order to destroy the sheet
music, he broke into the safe,

165
00:09:29.941 --> 00:09:33.841
but couldn't find the sheet
music, so he killed himself.

166
00:09:33.841 --> 00:09:34.551
No...

167
00:09:34.551 --> 00:09:36.191
I don't think he killed himself.

168
00:09:36.191 --> 00:09:36.701
What?

169
00:09:36.951 --> 00:09:40.461
Look closely at the spot
where the body's feet were.

170
00:09:40.701 --> 00:09:43.211
There's nothing there for him to step on.

171
00:09:43.541 --> 00:09:46.931
Normally a person wouldn't be able to
do that without a step of some kind.

172
00:09:46.931 --> 00:09:50.471
In other words, it's hard to
imagine that this was a suicide.

173
00:09:50.761 --> 00:09:52.721
I saw someone suspicious.

174
00:09:52.981 --> 00:09:53.831
What?

175
00:09:53.831 --> 00:09:55.851
There were two people in the piano room.

176
00:09:56.241 --> 00:10:01.451
One of them broke the window and fled,
but the other one was Murasawa.

177
00:10:01.451 --> 00:10:03.851
He was on the floor because
someone struck him.

178
00:10:03.851 --> 00:10:06.861
Doctor Narumi's examining him
in the piano room right now.

179
00:10:07.211 --> 00:10:08.871
You should've told us that sooner.

180
00:10:14.491 --> 00:10:17.811
Officer, did you find Aso-san's sheet music?

181
00:10:17.811 --> 00:10:18.331
No.

182
00:10:18.731 --> 00:10:21.661
After all, it happened 12 years ago.

183
00:10:22.021 --> 00:10:24.581
I have no idea where I put it.

184
00:10:25.851 --> 00:10:28.471
I believe he has a concussion,

185
00:10:28.471 --> 00:10:31.031
but I can't say for certain unless I
examine him properly at the clinic.

186
00:10:31.031 --> 00:10:32.541
I see.

187
00:10:32.541 --> 00:10:36.451
By the way, Kuroiwa-san, what
was Murasawa-san doing here?

188
00:10:36.451 --> 00:10:38.181
I don't know!

189
00:10:38.461 --> 00:10:40.681
I'd like to know the answer
to that question, too.

190
00:10:43.191 --> 00:10:44.001
What's this?

191
00:10:44.001 --> 00:10:44.981
Don't touch that!

192
00:10:45.571 --> 00:10:47.211
It belongs to Shuichi.

193
00:10:47.211 --> 00:10:48.521
What is that?

194
00:10:48.741 --> 00:10:51.941
I don't know, but it seemed important to him.

195
00:10:51.941 --> 00:10:56.031
That's a tuning hammer used to tune pianos.

196
00:10:56.611 --> 00:10:58.111
Does that mean he...?

197
00:10:59.181 --> 00:11:02.911
In any case, gather all the
suspects at the village office.

198
00:11:02.911 --> 00:11:04.581
We're going to interview them again.

199
00:11:04.581 --> 00:11:05.391
Yes, sir.

200
00:11:14.591 --> 00:11:16.091
What is it, Conan-kun?

201
00:11:16.441 --> 00:11:18.891
The suspicious person who
fled through the window

202
00:11:18.891 --> 00:11:21.931
was searching the bottom
of the piano before they ran.

203
00:11:22.171 --> 00:11:24.951
I thought there might be something here.

204
00:11:30.111 --> 00:11:31.821
What? Seriously?

205
00:11:31.821 --> 00:11:33.371
It's a secret door.

206
00:11:37.381 --> 00:11:38.951
What is this? Could it be?

207
00:11:49.378 --> 00:11:52.468
Judging by the methods used,

208
00:11:52.668 --> 00:11:54.388
the three murders that have taken place

209
00:11:54.388 --> 00:11:57.728
on this island were almost certainly
committed by the same person.

210
00:11:58.188 --> 00:11:59.518
What is it?

211
00:11:59.518 --> 00:12:01.728
Something's not right.

212
00:12:02.188 --> 00:12:06.958
Ever since I saw the code left at the second
crime scene, something has seemed strange.

213
00:12:07.538 --> 00:12:08.598
Inspector Megure.

214
00:12:09.338 --> 00:12:12.428
The photos we took of the scene of
Kuroiwa's murder have been developed.

215
00:12:12.908 --> 00:12:14.048
Thank you.

216
00:12:14.048 --> 00:12:15.778
Could you lay them out over there?

217
00:12:15.778 --> 00:12:16.428
Yes, sir.

218
00:12:17.078 --> 00:12:19.578
